            "id": "4411534",
            "title": "MercadoLibre shares rally as Q4 sales surge 37%",
            "description": "<html><body><p class=\"MsoNormal\">MercadoLibre (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\">NASDAQ:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/MELI\" title=\"MercadoLibre, Inc.\">MELI</a></span>) shares are rallying in Thursday’s after-hours trading after <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/news/4411473-mercadolibre-gaap-eps-of-12_61-beats-by-5_05-revenue-of-6_06b-beats-by-120m\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"fourth quarter results\">fourth quarter results</a> beat expectations as the company reported gains in all metrics including active buyers, gross merchandise volume, and payment volume, leading to a 37.4% increase in total sales.</p> <p class=\"MsoNormal paywall-full-content invisible\">“Mercado Libre had another great year in 2024, with more consumers and merchants choosing us, taking us past the milestones of 100M annual unique buyers and 60M Fintech MAUs for the first time,” the company said in a statement.</p> <p class=\"MsoNormal paywall-full-content invisible\">Led by a 33% gain in total payment volume, and 8% increase in gross merchandise volume (“GMV”), total sales of $6.1B exceeded Wall Street’s expectations by $120M, and contributed to a profit of $12.61 per share, nearly 4x more than a year ago.</p> <p class=\"MsoNormal paywall-full-content invisible\">Brazil, which represents the majority of MercadoLibre’s (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\">NASDAQ:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/MELI\" title=\"MercadoLibre, Inc.\">MELI</a></span>) revenue, saw a 13% gain in GMV and 38% surge in consolidated revenue and financial income.</p> <p class=\"MsoNormal paywall-full-content invisible\">Shares are <span style=\"color: #008000;\">up 13%. </span></p> </body></html>",
            "image": "https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1306864981/image_1306864981.jpg",
            "link": "https://seekingalpha.com/news/4411534-mercadolibre-shares-rally-as-q4-sales-surge-37",
